						<summary>

						<p>Slab set up infront of the shrine of Rāma.</p>						

						<p>This is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1071, Jyeshṭha śu. 1,</hi> corresponding to 1149 A.D.</p>						

						<p>Very much damaged. It refers to the date portion and mentions the imprecatory portion and also Lankamat[syakēśvara and Akāśa]bhairava.</p>						

						</summary>
